  "translations": {
    "en": {
      "description": {
        "text": "Noret is the collective name for the crags around the marina south of Klövberget. There are some fine and distinctive routes here, mixed in with a fair amount of dross.",
        "method": "llm",
        "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
        "sourceIds": [
          "legacy:noret"
        ]
      },
      "sections": {
        "allmant": {
          "title": {
            "text": "General",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:noret"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "Noret is a collective name for the crags around the boat harbour south of Klövberget. There are some fine and unique routes here, mixed in with a fair amount of rubbish.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:noret"
            ]
          }
        },
        "beskrivning": {
          "title": {
            "text": "Description",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:noret"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "There is plenty of rock here, though much of it is uninteresting for climbing. So far, five areas have been climbed: the crags just beyond the descent to the jetties; the slab to the right of the steps leading up the hillside; the steep wall on the right after crossing the jetties; the short wall high above and behind the large boulder field; and the wall furthest to the left.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:noret"
            ]
          }
        },
        "miljo": {
          "title": {
            "text": "Aspect",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:noret"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "South-west-facing and mostly open to the sun.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:noret"
            ]
          }
        },
        "vagbeskrivning": {
          "title": {
            "text": "Directions",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:noret"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "Follow the directions for Klövberget, but continue past the car park and turn right onto Svartbäcksvägen. Follow it until a steep hill leads down to the water. Turn sharply right here onto Noretvägen and continue until a small road/path branches off to the right. Park here. The path leads down to the boat harbour.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:noret"
            ]
          }
        },
        "leder": {
          "title": {
            "text": "Routes",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:noret"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:noret"
            ]
          }
        },
        "terriervaggen": {
          "title": {
            "text": "Terrierväggen",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:noret"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "Overhanging wall with a boulder in front. There is no topo for the left-hand section.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:noret"
            ]
          }
        },
        "roda-lacket-klippan": {
          "title": {
            "text": "Röda Lacket crag",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:noret"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "50 m north of the boat harbour is a low but steep, slightly reddish crag. The easiest way to reach it is to go left of the boulders, though it is also possible to scramble up on the right-hand side.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:noret"
            ]
          }
        },
        "bathamnen": {
          "title": {
            "text": "The boat harbour",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:noret"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "Just beyond the jetties is a huge boulder with a fine low-level traverse and various vertical boulder problems. Behind it is a steep, compact wall with several overhangs and a finishing roof reminiscent of Klövberget.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:noret"
            ]
          }
        },
        "sprackliga-bandet": {
          "title": {
            "text": "Spräckliga bandet",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:noret"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "The next slab, which leads up to a ledge with a logical but apparently quite thin finish above, has probably not been climbed. By the boat harbour, steps lead up the hillside. To the right of these is a route up the very distinctively patterned slab.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:noret"
            ]
          }
        },
        "ormplattan": {
          "title": {
            "text": "Ormplattan",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:noret"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "20 m beyond the car park is a high section of crag with several steep slabs.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:noret"
            ]
          }
        },
        "svartbacksvaggen": {
          "title": {
            "text": "Svartbäcksväggen",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:noret"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "Small wall on the slope above Svartbäcksvägen, a couple of hundred metres before Noretvägen.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:noret"
            ]
          }
        },
        "extern-forare": {
          "title": {
            "text": "External guide",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:noret"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "Several walls are included in Stockholms Nätförare (http://www.plonk.se/snf/noret.html)",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:noret"
            ]
          }
        }
      },
      "routes": {
        "noret-led-20": {
          "description": {
            "text": "The obvious offwidth crack with two chockstones to the right of ‘the lone bolt’. From the ledge, the finish goes straight up the crack. Surely it must have been climbed before? – If it is the crack/corner in the corner, then surely it is ‘Ettan’? If not, it is the start of ‘Grov Portion’.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:noret"
            ]
          }
        },
        "noret-led-23": {
          "description": {
            "text": "Alternative finish to Ettan. Climb Ettan/the crack straight up to the roof, then move right and continue up the offwidth crack in the corner before rounding the roof. Fun climbing.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:noret"
            ]
          }
        },
        "noret-led-24": {
          "description": {
            "text": "Alternative finish to Isbiten. Halfway up Isbiten, branch off left to a short crux on small crimps. Then head up left to a separate anchor.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:noret"
            ]
          }
        },
        "noret-led-25": {
          "description": {
            "text": "Fine bolted route on the side wall. The start was rebolted in -09.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:noret"
            ]
          }
        },
        "noret-led-26": {
          "description": {
            "text": "Poor protection. The rusty bolt has been removed. One rusty old piton remains. Should not be led.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:noret"
            ]
          }
        },
        "noret-led-27": {
          "description": {
            "text": "Starts through the small roof.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:noret"
            ]
          }
        },
        "noret-led-28": {
          "description": {
            "text": "Vertical climbing. Hard until you work it out.",
